Description:
Bespoke design meets period grace
This superbly renovated Californian Bungalow defies expectations with a combination of chic Scandinavian style & a serenity that delights the senses. The immaculate interior features stunning natural timber floorboards & classic period elements combining with fittings only seen in the finest of homes. The ambient living room is enhanced by natural light & continues into the open plan dining room & culinary kitchen equipped with stone benches, including an island bench with breakfast bar & stainless-steel Bosch & LG appliances. Delivering immense indoor-outdoor allure, the north facing, decked courtyard garden is complemented by brilliant entertaining options & an outdoor toilet. Elegant period grace & built-in wardrobes complete the main & second bedrooms, both served by a stunning bathroom with a shower-over-bath, black tapware & nearby a cleverly concealed Euro laundry. A huge, private manicured front garden, ceiling fans, ducted heating, split-system cooling, video intercom, electric gates & a retractable ladder to the attic with potential (STCA). Only minutes to Kilvington Grammar School, Ormond train station, EE Gunn Reserve & Glen Huntly Primary School.

Description:
Neat, Tidy, and Close To It All
This cheerful two-bedroom apartment is in a great location, close to Ormond shops, the train station, and only a short drive from pristine Brighton Beach. Featuring two generously sized bedrooms with built-in robes, the living room features access to the balcony. Living and dining room is ample, right next to the modern styled kitchen and meals area. Also includes:
- Heating system
- One car space
- Modern style bathroom and laundry
- Close to Kilvington Grammar, kindergartens, and Ormond Primary
- A few minutes walk to Ormond's speciality cafes and shops
- Close to Ormond Railway Station and buses
A perfect investment property or first home that's close to the city and the beach in the South East. There will be a lot of interest, so get in quick by calling our agent Lori Ille on 0490815632 and securing your viewing.

Description:
A c1926 Californian classic two doors from the park
First time offered in 92 years, this one owner 2 bedroom + study brick Californian Bungalow on 683sqm approx is full of classic comfort and exceptional potential. Warm and inviting with lovely character, this well built gem enjoys a double door entry, 2 large bedrooms (BIRs), charming lounge & dining rooms (OFPs, gas heater), galley kitchen/laundry with TV/meals area, a central bathroom, sun filled study, 2nd toilet and an alarm. The deep east-facing rear garden has lovely space to extend or subdivide (STCA) in tranquil privacy. A glorious family home in this parkside setting, metres to Mr Brightside Café, the Chadstone bus & Caufield South Primary School, walk to Booran Reserve. *Please click on our interactive Floorplans & Interactive Tour links to update the kitchen using our photo styling tools or to utilise our furnishing and measuring service.

Description:
Perfectly positioned for a cafe lifestyle
An enviable cafe lifestyle awaits at this beautifully presented 2-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom town residence just moments to the beating heart of vibrant Ormond village. In a peaceful and contemporary group, this impeccable home is a brilliant proposition for busy commuters and first home buyers seeking an easy-care slice of a burgeoning suburb where all essential amenities are within arm's reach.
With the peace of mind of secure intercom entry, this stylishly appointed home features two ground floor bedrooms (BIRs), both benefiting from their own sleek ensuites. Perfect for that first morning coffee, the rear bedroom spills out to a sundrenched private terrace. Upstairs is a sun-filled entertainer's zone where lofty ceilings and well-placed windows bring in streams of natural light. A luxurious stone kitchen with premium Smeg appliances overlooks this fabulous space to a broad, powered balcony.
Only five years old, this appealing home also features powder room, double basement garage with laundry, substantial storage plus split system heating and cooling throughout. Walk to shops, station, restaurants and all necessities from this chic, hassle-free home.

Description:
A Modern Marvel of Easy Living
Well maintained with its own street frontage, this tastefully updated 3 bedroom 60s villa has some modern sophistication with its stylish outdoor living. Standing out proudly from its peers thanks to a simply huge alfresco terrace, this renovated two-bedroom apartment is one out of the box! Metres from Ormond's restaurant and cafe scene, and just moments from the station, head out to enjoy what's on offer then escape to your exclusive garden retreat.

Description:
A Deco Discovery of Easy Family Living
In beautifully manicured gardens making the home quite private from the street, this enchanting 3 bedroom + study 2.5 bathroom Art Deco beauty captures the heart and soul of family living on a compact block. Welcomed by a terrazzo verandah and double door entry, this engaging treasure features a wide entry hall, a gorgeous sitting room flowing to the engaging dining room (OFP), the relaxed family living/dining area and the stunning stone kitchen (Fisher & Paykel appliances including dish drawers, Miele cooktop, soft close cabinetry & large pantry); a beautiful downstairs main bedroom (bay window, WIR & ensuite), fitted study nook, laundry and powder room. Upstairs there are 2 further large bedrooms (BIRs) and a stylish bathroom. A covered deck with synthetic lawn area makes it easy to give small children outdoor spaces to play, while the front garden is secure for additional space to enjoy the sun. Exquisite with its leadlights, high intricate ceilings and deep sills, this heartwarming home provides security doors, ducted heating, split system air conditioning, evaporative cooling, ducted vacuum, video intercom, keyless entry, pre-wired for home theatre and auto gates to parking for 2. In the McKinnon Secondary College zone, between funky North Road eateries and McKinnon Village cafes, walk to train, Allnutt Park and Ormond Primary School.

A Prime Opportunity in an Iconic Street
Here is a special property in iconic Malane Street, which is lined by charming homes from the Californian Bungalow era. To maintain the period integrity of the streetscape, a heritage overlay has been attached to the facades of the residences, making this a truly delightful enclave and a highly desirable residential area.
There is no doubt that the next owners of this property will want to modernise and perhaps extend the weary old 3-bedroom home that has obviously done sterling service. Apart from that innately warm ambience found in homes of this era - and also high ceilings, well proportioned rooms, and a noteworthy pair of leadlight windows in one of the two living rooms - not many period features remain here. Yet there is so much promise! It is easy to imagine the very essence of the era restored to the front rooms of the home and then a modern addition bringing today's comforts into play. Then again, a sleek contemporary abode hiding behind a period façade could be the way to go. Whatever the decision for the future of this residence, it is a win-win situation.
The home - occupying a prime allotment (approx. 670sqm) with the bonus of rear access to Fraser Street - is located with EE Gunn Reserve at one end of the street and nearby shops, cafes, trains, buses, schools and recreation.

Description:
Exceptional design. Every modern convenience imaginable
This picture perfect, immaculately presented, architecturally designed masterpiece has a hint of period charm & every modern convenience imaginable. Featuring perfectly landscaped gardens with lighting & irrigation, solid spotted gum floorboards, plantation shutters & 3m high ceilings throughout. Main bedroom with polished ensuite & walk in robe, two further bedrooms with built in robes, a sparking central family bathroom & the flexibility of a fourth bedroom/lounge. A contemporary, fully equipped Smart-stone kitchen with quality Ilve appliances & Asko dishwasher flows into a light filled, living/dining & alfresco area of generous proportions & unsurpassed style. This exceptional family home comes complete with a long list of life enhancing technology including video surveillance & alarm, C-Bus program controlled lighting, SpeakerCraft sound system, 12 000 litre underground water tank, zoned heating & cooling, Rinnai water temperature control, ducted vacuuming & an automatic double garage. All within exceptional proximity to Packer Park, Koornang Road shops, transport & within the sought after McKinnon Primary School zone.

Description:
Effortless Excellence and Lifestyle
Quality accentuates the contemporary family lifestyle of this impressive 4 bedroom 3 bathroom street front sensation. Beautifully warm with Grey Ironbark floors, this designer haven enjoys a downstairs guest bedroom with adjoining well-equipped bathroom/laundry; and north facing open plan entertaining with radiant stone kitchen (Miele appliances including induction cooktop) that seamlessly opens onto a generous sun drenched Merbau deck surrounded by Kaye Parris Magnolias. Upstairs you'll find a gorgeous master bedroom (balcony, fitted WIR & chic ensuite), 2 spacious bedrooms (fitted BIRs) and a fully tiled porcelain bathroom with separate toilet. With loads of warmth and vitality, this terrific home enjoys ducted heating & refrigerated air conditioning, video intercom, alarm, stone benchtops, thoughtful storage, double blinds, a rainwater tank, auto garage and an exposed aggregate driveway. In this beautiful tree lined street at the no through road end, a heartbeat to North Road shops, cafes, train and Monash University bus, minutes to a choice of schools and glorious parks.

Description:
This College Zone Secret Garden is a Class Act!
Discover your 'secret garden' in the heart of the College Zone commuter precinct! Just one block from the McKinnon Rd retail and rail strip and a walk to McKinnon Secondary College, this secluded single level townhouse comes with clever two bedroom, 1.5 bathroom accommodation, as new presentation and secluded courtyard gardens with a sun catching northern orientation.
Cleverly designed with an airy open plan flowing to decking and a quiet bedroom wing including a fan cooled master with lush green outlooks, this well designed single level home is hidden away in the group's quietest rear position with a well-placed auto garage ensuring no shared walls and bonus visitor parking right at the door.
Styled with a state of the art Smeg appliance kitchen and designer bathroom plus a large powder room, all the first class finishes are here - including stone benchtops, glossy hardwood floors and block out blinds. Centrally heated with air-conditioner, there are even added energy efficiencies including solar panels, a 2000L water tank and climate controlling tinted glazing.
With cafes at the end of the street, the station around the corner and the College in Zone, this better than new single level home is a class act!

Description:
Enjoy the location, love the privacy
In a boutique, well maintained block of only eight apartments, this ground floor beauty is just perfect for those wanting a lock up & leave lifestyle. Freshly painted throughout, the home enjoys a gas, eat-in kitchen with good storage, light-filled living & dining room opening on the outdoor space, two generous, carpeted bedrooms both with robes & a large bathroom. But the real bonus is what’s outside; a very private wrap-around courtyard (with a laundry & storage space as well as extra toilet), ideal for those who want an easy-care lifestyle, but still love the idea of outdoor entertaining. Also featuring a lock up garage, split system air conditioning & secure entry. Perfectly located in a lovely, leafy street just a five-minute walk to Ormond trains & cafes, private & government schools, stroll to the Monash Uni bus, an abundance of parkland & just a short drive to the beaches of Port Phillip Bay. This is private & tranquil living at its best; a perfect first home, great downsize option or investment opportunity.
